    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>thinly into rounds (chop any larger pieces in half)</p><p>Drain the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Add both to a baking tray, lined with <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong>, with the <strong>harissa paste</strong>, a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until evenly coated</p><p>Put into the oven for 20-25 min or until the aubergine is cooked through</p>",
